The project consists of: (a) a rockfill
            dam on the Shire River at Nkula site; (b) a pressure cut and
            cover conduit, head racetunnel, penstock and tailrace outlet
            system and a power house for five 18-MW hydro units; (c) two
            18-MW hydro units as the first stage of the 90-MW ultimate
            development; (d) consulting services; and (e) training.
